:: Inventory [nobr]
/%
        Floating-window tab content (auto-registered because this passage
        exists). Renders the full inventory UI via the <<inventoryView>>
        macro defined in 11-inventory.twee.

        Layout (per spec):
          +-------------------+----------+
          | Inventory         |          |
          | (66%w × 80%h)     | Equipped |
          | search + filters  | (33%w ×  |
          +-------------------+  100%h)  |
          | Outfit Sets       |          |
          | (66%w × 20%h)     |          |
          +-------------------+----------+

        The view is fully driven by $inventory, $equipped and $outfitSets
        state. Action buttons (use / inspect / equip / unequip / drop)
        mutate state and call setup.ui.refresh(), which re-renders both
        this view and the right sidebar (avatar + stats).
%/
<<inventoryView>>

:: Quests [nobr]
/%
        Floating-window tab content. Renders the full quest log via the
        <<questLog>> macro defined in 12-quests.twee.

        Quests are catalog-driven: $quests = { active:[], completed:[] }
        stores only quest ids; everything else (title, description,
        subquests, status) is read from setup.quests.catalog at render
        time. Subquest status is *validated* — each subquest's status()
        function checks state variables and returns "not_started",
        "in_progress", "completed", or "failed".

        Start a quest from any story passage with <<questStart "id">>
        and complete it with <<questComplete "id">>.
%/
<<questLog>>
